==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Godwit
<hw>God"wit</hw> <pr>(g⟦ocr⟧d"w⟦icr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob.
from AS. <ets>g⟦omac⟧d</ets> good + <ets>wiht</ets> creature,
wight.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of several species of
long-billed, wading birds of the genus <gen>Limosa</gen>, and family
<fam>Tringid⟦ae⟧</fam>. The European black-tailed godwit (<spn>Limosa
limosa</spn>), the American marbled godwit (<spn>Limosa fedoa</spn>),
the Hudsonian godwit (<spn>Limosa h⟦ae⟧mastica</spn>), and others, are
valued as game birds. Called also <altname>godwin</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Goel</ent>⟦br⟧
